#. <section class="sutta" id="an10.113"><article><div class="hgroup"><p class="division">
msgctxt "an10.113:0.1"
msgid "Aṅguttara Nikāya 10"
msgstr "Numbered Discourses 10"

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "an10.113:0.2"
msgid "12. Paccorohaṇivagga"
msgstr "12. The Ceremony of Descent"

#. </p><h1>
msgctxt "an10.113:0.3"
msgid "113. Paṭhamaadhammasutta"
msgstr "113. Bad Principles (1st)"

# Here and following BB’s translation is less than ideal. Dhamma is not translated, and attha/anattha is, I think, mistranslated. Here it is clearly the result of the dhamma. The point is not that it is “beneficial”, i.e. that is creates benefit, but that it is a benefit created by the dhamma. Dhamma is cause, attha effect.<a class="sc" id="sc1"></a>
#. </h1></div><p>
msgctxt "an10.113:0.4"
msgid "“Adhammo ca, bhikkhave, veditabbo anattho ca;"
msgstr "“Mendicants, you should know bad principles with bad results."

msgctxt "an10.113:0.5"
msgid "dhammo ca veditabbo attho ca."
msgstr "And you should know good principles with good results."

msgctxt "an10.113:0.6"
msgid ""
"Adhammañca viditvā anatthañca, dhammañca viditvā atthañca yathā dhammo yathā "
"attho tathā paṭipajjitabbaṃ."
msgstr ""
"Knowing these things, your practice should follow the good principles with "
"good results."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="pts-vp-pi" id="pts-vp-pi5.223"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc2"></a>
msgctxt "an10.113:2.1"
msgid "Katamo ca, bhikkhave, adhammo ca anattho ca?"
msgstr "And what are bad principles with bad results?"

msgctxt "an10.113:2.2"
msgid ""
"Micchādiṭṭhi, micchāsaṅkappo, micchāvācā, micchākammanto, micchāājīvo, "
"micchāvāyāmo, micchāsati, micchāsamādhi, micchāñāṇaṃ, micchāvimutti—"
msgstr ""
"Wrong view, wrong thought, wrong speech, wrong action, wrong livelihood, "
"wrong effort, wrong mindfulness, wrong immersion, wrong knowledge, and wrong "
"freedom."

msgctxt "an10.113:2.3"
msgid "ayaṃ vuccati, bhikkhave, adhammo ca anattho ca."
msgstr "These are called bad principles with bad results."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc3"></a>
msgctxt "an10.113:3.1"
msgid "Katamo ca, bhikkhave, dhammo ca attho ca?"
msgstr "And what are good principles with good results?"

msgctxt "an10.113:3.2"
msgid ""
"Sammādiṭṭhi, sammāsaṅkappo, sammāvācā, sammākammanto, sammāājīvo, "
"sammāvāyāmo, sammāsati, sammāsamādhi, sammāñāṇaṃ, sammāvimutti—"
msgstr ""
"Right view, right thought, right speech, right action, right livelihood, "
"right effort, right mindfulness, right immersion, right knowledge, and right "
"freedom."

msgctxt "an10.113:3.3"
msgid "ayaṃ vuccati, bhikkhave, dhammo ca attho ca."
msgstr "These are called good principles with good results."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc4"></a>
msgctxt "an10.113:4.1"
msgid "‘Adhammo ca, bhikkhave, veditabbo anattho ca;"
msgstr "‘You should know bad principles with bad results."

msgctxt "an10.113:4.2"
msgid "dhammo ca veditabbo attho ca."
msgstr "And you should know good principles with good results."

msgctxt "an10.113:4.3"
msgid ""
"Adhammañca viditvā anatthañca, dhammañca viditvā atthañca yathā dhammo yathā "
"attho tathā paṭipajjitabban’ti, "
msgstr ""
"Knowing these things, your practice should follow the good principles with "
"good results.’ "

msgctxt "an10.113:4.4"
msgid "iti yaṃ taṃ vuttaṃ, idametaṃ paṭicca vuttan”ti."
msgstr "That’s what I said, and this is why I said it.”"

#. </p><p class="endsection">
msgctxt "an10.113:4.5"
msgid "Paṭhamaṃ."
msgstr ""
